This paper deals with the restricted isometry property of subsampled Fourier matrices, which is a topic in both information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS). The use of Fourier matrices also suggests a connection to numerical analysis (cs.NA). The paper also discusses the sparsity of vectors, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and signal processing (cs.SI).
